This #NationalTourismDay, pledge to reduce coral reef destruction during your trips. The world has already lost 27% of its coral reefs, destroyed due to climate change, overfishing & unsustainable tourism practices. Some scientists think, by 2070, coral reefs could be gone altogether! Dive responsibly, use reef-safe sunscreen, don't pollute the sea with plastic or collect live corals, and skip eating endangered fish species to protect precious corals. ​

​[Tourism, Sustainable, Plastic, Tourists, Corals, Climate ]

#TourismDay #Tourism #CoralReef #EndangeredCorals #Sustainablity

This #nationaltourismday, pledge to reduce paper consumption during your trips. It is estimated that about 17 trees & 2,700 litres of water are needed to produce 1 tonne of paper. Overall paper consumption makes for 33-40% of the world’s commercially cut timber. Paper also accounts for 26% of waste in landfills & emits toxic methane gas when it rots. You can play your part by booking your travel online, carrying digital tickets & using E-Visa, DigiYatra etc.​

​[ Tourism Day, Tourism, Save paper, Go digital]

#tourismday #tourism #gopaperless #savepaper #godigital #digiyatra
